## 3. Raycast (raycast.com)

Raycast blends extreme functional utility with beautiful, subtle motion. Their site is heavily skewed toward showing exactly what the product does through static UI snippets.

### Global Navigation Hierarchy
`Store` • `Pro` • `AI` • `iOS` • `Windows` • `Teams` • `Developers` • `Blog` • [Pricing](file:///c:/Users/abe/OneDrive/NexaOS/src/pages/Pricing.tsx#6-96) • `Log in` • **[ Download ]**

### Exact Homepage Section Order
1. **The Hero:** "Your shortcut to everything." (Primary CTA: "Download for Mac").
2. **Feature Showcase Scroll:** A chronological scroll highlighting core utilities linearly (Clipboard, Snippets, Window Management).
3. **Ecosystem Proof:** Showcasing the "1,500+ extensions" store.
4. **AI Capabilities Block.**
5. **The Feature Bento Box:** A 3-block grid highlighting hotkeys and aliases.
6. **Productivity Tiers:** Breakdown of Pro vs. Teams features.
7. **Performance Bento Box:** A 4-column grid selling the "Speed" aspect ("Fast, Ergonomic, Native, Reliable").
8. **Social Proof Wall:** Wall-to-wall tweets/quotes from power users.
9. **Final CTA.**

