## What this means for NexaOS (V2 Spec Validation)

This hard evidence validates the V2 Spec we drafted:
*   **The Global Nav is strictly constrained.** (Raycast, Linear, and Vercel all use a single, highly-contrast Primary CTA button on the far right. No emojis).
*   **The "Linear" Hero structure is ubiquitous.** (Oversized H1 directly followed by the Product UI or an interactive selector, avoiding abstract illustrations).
*   **The Bento Box is the industry standard for feature presentation.** (We will use this exact structure for the "Missed Call / Reviews / Pipeline" features).
